{{Infobox dot-com company |name = Preply |logo = File:Preply,_logo.png |logo alt = |collapsible = <!-- "yes" or "no" --> |screenshot = |screenshot size = <!-- width in pixels, with "px" suffix --> |screenshot alt = |caption = |type = [[Privately held company|Private]] |traded as = |founded = <!-- {{start date and age|year|month|day}} --> |dissolved = <!-- {{start date and age|year|month|day}} --> |predecessor = |successor = |location = [[Brighton, Massachusetts]] |country = [[US]] |country of origin = |locations = |area served = |founder = Serge Lukianov, Kirill Bigai, Dmytro Voloshyn |chairman = |chairperson = |president = |CEO = Kirill Bigai |MD = |GM = |key people = |industry = [[Online education]] |products = |services = Education service |revenue = |operating income = |international = yes |net income = |assets = |equity = |owner = |employees = 50 |parent = |divisions = |subsidiaries = |slogan = |url = {{URL|https://preply.com}} |programming language = |ipv6 = |alexa = {{increase}} 35,798 ({{as of |2017|07|18|alt= July 2017}})<ref name="alexa">{{cite web|url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/preply.com|title=Preply|publisher= [[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate=July 18, 2017}}</ref> |website type = |advertising = |registration = |users = |language = |launched = {{start date and age|2012|11|1}} |current status = Online |native clients = |footnotes = |coordinates = }}
'''Preply''' is an [[online]] [[educational technology]] platform which pairs [[student]]s with private [[tutor]]s, either locally in-person or remotely via [[Skype]]. It features a ranking algorithm which uses [[machine learning]] for classification and recommendation of tutors.<ref name=TechCrunch>{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/06/07/preply-pulls-in-1-3m-to-expand-its-tutoring-marketplace-in-europe/|title=Preply pulls in $1.3M to expand its tutoring marketplace in Europe|publisher=[[TechCrunch]]|first=Natasha|last=Lomas|date=7 June 2016|access-date=18 July 2017|language= |trans-title=}}</ref>
==History== At [[IDCEE]] (Internet Technologies & Innovations) 2012, Preply was chosen as one of the most promising [[startup company|startup companies]] in [[Ukraine]].<ref name=Fokus1>{{cite web|url=https://focus.ua/lifestyle/247826/|title=Большие надежды. ТОП-30 стартапов украинского интернета|publisher=|first=|last=|date=19 October 2012|access-date=18 July 2017|language=[[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] |trans-title=The Most Promising Hopefuls. Top 30 Ukrainian Internet Start-ups}}</ref> Afterwards, the [[Startup company|startup]] was picked up by Eastlabs, and following an initial investment of $175,000 from Vostok Ventures as well as business angels [[Semyon Dukach]] and Torben Majgaard,<ref name=UDN>{{cite web|url=http://www.uadn.net/2015/02/02/online-tutoring-platform-preply-enters-polish-market/|title=Ukrainian online tutoring platform Preply enters Polish market|publisher=Ukraine Digital News|first= |last=|date=2 February 2015|access-date=18 July 2017}}</ref> its site, preply.com, was launched in November 2012.<ref name=KyivPost1>{{cite web|url=https://www.kyivpost.com/article/guide/people/connecting-language-tutors-and-students-via-skype-323454.html|title=Connecting language tutors and students via Skype|publisher=Kyiv Post|first=Elena|last=Pashkovskaya|date=18 April 2013|access-date=18 July 2017|language=|trans-title=}}</ref> Co-founded by Serge Lukianov, Dmytro Voloshyn, and Kirill Bigai – who serves as its current CEO<ref name=crunchbase>{{cite web|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/findguru-me#/entity|title=Preply.com|publisher=CrunchBase|first= |last=|date=|access-date=July 18, 2017}}</ref> – the company initially entered the Ukrainian, Russian, Belarussian and Kazakhstani markets, before expanding to the Polish market<ref name=UDN></ref> and receiving a $120,000 [[TechStars]] [[Berlin]] investment.<ref name=AIN>{{cite web|url=https://ain.ua/2015/07/09/ukrainskij-startap-preply-popal-v-techstars-poluchil-120-000-investicij-i-uezzhaet-v-berlin|title=Украинский стартап Preply попал в TechStars, получил $120 000 инвестиций и уезжает в Берлин|publisher=Ain|first=Майя|last=Яровая|date=9 February 2017|access-date=18 July 2017|language=[[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]]|trans-title=Ukrainian startup Preply got to TechStars, received $ 120,000 investment and left for Berlin}}</ref> At the beginning of 2016, the company entered the Brazilian market.<ref name=KyivPost2>{{cite web|url=https://www.kyivpost.com/article/content/ukraines-it-edge/ukrainian-online-tutoring-platform-enters-brazilian-market-406838.html|title=Ukrainian online tutoring platform enters Brazilian market|publisher=Kyiv Post|first=Denys|last=Krasnikov|date=28 January 2016|access-date=18 July 2017|language=|trans-title=}}</ref> After closing a $1.3 million seed round in June 2016, Preply has announced intentions of expanding its services to three more markets: [[UK]], [[Germany]], and [[Spain]].<ref name=TechCrunch></ref>
==Services== A February 2017 EuropaWire article stated that Preply had 47,000 registered tutors, offering help in as many as 40 different subjects, 27 of which were languages courses.<ref name=EuropaWire>{{cite web|url=http://news.europawire.eu/88000-preply-plateforme-damelioration-continue-pour-le-tutorat-et-les-etudes-en-ligne-arrive-en-france/eu-press-release/2017/02/09/|title=Preply, plateforme d'amélioration continue pour le tutorat et les études en ligne, arrive en France|publisher=EuropaWire|first=|last=|date=9 February 2017|access-date=18 July 2017|language=[[French language|French]]|trans-title=Preply, a platform for continuous improvement, tutoring and online studies, arrives in France}}</ref> As of July 2017, as per the company's statistics, almost 100,000 students have successfully found a tutor using the platform.<ref name=Preply.com>{{cite web|url=https://preply.com/|title=Preply.com|publisher=|first=|last=|date=|access-date=18 July 2017|language=|trans-title=}}</ref> It is estimated that tutors give about 30,000 hours of lessons per month at a price varying anywhere between $2 and $100.<ref name=EuropaWire></ref>
